WEBVTT

00:00.024 --> 00:01.565
Previously on "Devious Maids"...

00:01.616 --> 00:03.097
Peter. Husband number three.

00:03.147 --> 00:04.785
Please stop dating Peter.

00:04.835 --> 00:06.342
I'm not breaking up with him.

00:06.392 --> 00:07.555
A little birdie told me

00:07.605 --> 00:10.071
that Marisol got
back together with Jesse.

00:10.121 --> 00:12.512
I am with Peter now.
You have to accept that.

00:12.562 --> 00:15.473
You were right.
Marisol's seeing her ex again.

00:16.369 --> 00:17.762
I know you're my mother now.

00:17.812 --> 00:19.417
I'm not your mother, Danni.

00:19.467 --> 00:20.978
I gave you up for a reason.

00:21.028 --> 00:23.017
From now on, you're nothing to me.

00:23.067 --> 00:24.135
I'm leaving you.

00:24.185 --> 00:25.910
Evelyn, we were meant to be together.

00:25.960 --> 00:27.386
Oh, you're the reverend. Hello.

00:27.436 --> 00:30.599
I was afraid you might be
a bit of a... goody-goody.

00:30.649 --> 00:31.541
I'm no saint.

00:31.591 --> 00:32.729
My wife believes he's the greatest man

00:32.780 --> 00:33.709
that ever walked the Earth.

00:33.759 --> 00:34.804
I intend to prove her wrong.

00:34.854 --> 00:38.012
There's no reason to deny
the deep sexual tension

00:38.062 --> 00:39.061
between us.

00:39.111 --> 00:41.444
Is it possible you're unclear on
the meaning of sexual tension?

00:41.494 --> 00:44.226
You think Kyle and Frances
are in a cult?

00:44.276 --> 00:45.984
If he were in a cult, I would know.

00:46.034 --> 00:48.748
Like he knows you're a
maid pretending to be rich?

00:48.798 --> 00:50.789
We finally have your mother's blessing.

00:50.839 --> 00:52.862
You know, Kyle, maybe you
should move back home.

00:52.912 --> 00:54.375
Not being roommates could bring back

00:54.425 --> 00:56.171
some of that romance we've been missing.

00:56.221 --> 00:57.030
We'd like to check the attic.

00:57.080 --> 00:58.198
You don't have to do that.

00:58.248 --> 00:59.685
I noticed Kyle and his mom

00:59.735 --> 01:01.923
being really secretive about the attic.

01:01.973 --> 01:03.185
- Ben?
- I still need to find

01:03.235 --> 01:05.537
the video of Peri confessing her secret.

01:05.587 --> 01:07.724
Maybe that's where they keep the videos.

01:07.774 --> 01:09.084
I can drum up some reason

01:09.134 --> 01:10.733
to sneak in there and snoop around.

01:10.783 --> 01:11.768
I'm Fiona.

01:11.818 --> 01:12.909
I thought you were... in Italy.

01:12.959 --> 01:14.383
You must be Zoila, my maid.

01:22.146 --> 01:24.018
Morning.
-Kyle!

01:24.697 --> 01:25.844
What are you doing here?

01:25.953 --> 01:27.909
I want to take my honey
out to breakfast.

01:27.964 --> 01:28.782
Surprise.

01:28.832 --> 01:30.405
Surprise!

01:30.672 --> 01:32.522
Um, sorry.

01:32.572 --> 01:36.790
Uh... I'm in the middle
of cleaning the house.

01:37.464 --> 01:38.492
The maid didn't show up?

01:38.542 --> 01:39.491
Nope.

01:39.941 --> 01:42.351
She hasn't really been focused
on her job lately.

01:42.401 --> 01:44.360
Sounds like someone's gonna get fired.

01:44.834 --> 01:46.784
That's a real possibility.

01:46.976 --> 01:48.165
How about tomorrow night?

01:48.215 --> 01:50.280
Oh, I'm taking my mother to dinner.

01:50.416 --> 01:51.901
So, you and Frances will
be out of the house?

01:51.951 --> 01:53.178
Just for a couple hours.

01:53.228 --> 01:55.194
- Zoila!
- Who's that?

01:55.244 --> 01:58.533
Um, I have a friend in from out of town.

01:58.583 --> 01:59.416
She got in last night.

01:59.466 --> 02:00.524
Oh, yeah? I'd love to meet her.

02:00.574 --> 02:02.575
No! No. She's very sick.

02:02.625 --> 02:03.918
I don't want you to catch it.

02:03.968 --> 02:05.049
Call me later.

02:11.128 --> 02:12.235
There you are.

02:12.535 --> 02:13.345
Who was that?

02:13.395 --> 02:14.984
Um, just a neighbor.

02:15.151 --> 02:17.850
So, are you settling in okay?

02:17.900 --> 02:19.953
Yes. But it's very strange.

02:20.003 --> 02:23.432
My clothes all seem to be stretched out,

02:23.766 --> 02:26.267
as though they've been worn
by a great big fat person.

02:26.976 --> 02:30.261
Well, no big fat
person has worn your clothes.

02:30.389 --> 02:31.729
I promise.

02:32.475 --> 02:34.384
Zoila, perhaps now would be a good time

02:34.434 --> 02:36.855
for me to clarify my
expectations for you.

02:36.941 --> 02:39.397
Firstly... and this is important...

02:39.908 --> 02:42.055
I expect you to come running
when I call for you.

02:42.105 --> 02:42.905
Like a dog?

02:42.918 --> 02:45.255
Oh, no, not at all.

02:45.305 --> 02:46.468
But, yes, exactly.

02:46.518 --> 02:49.941
Also, my meals will be served
in the formal dining room.

02:50.202 --> 02:51.542
And I'd rather prefer it if you don't

02:51.592 --> 02:53.386
have personal visitors to the house.

02:53.604 --> 02:54.553
Got it.

02:54.603 --> 02:55.705
Lastly,

02:56.106 --> 02:58.366
I like to project a certain image,

02:58.776 --> 03:02.919
so, from now on,
you'll wear a maid's uniform.

03:02.969 --> 03:05.883
Is that really necessary?

03:05.933 --> 03:07.706
It is. When people come by,

03:07.756 --> 03:10.069
they need to know exactly who you are.

03:16.759 --> 03:22.429
